OL,3,CThe parents who have pledged to keep
OL,4,Ctheir kids smartphone-free
OL,6,FITV West Country's Bob Cruwys has been
OL,7,Fspeaking to some of those behind the
OL,8,Fpledge
OL,10,FA group of parents in North Devon have
OL,11,Fclubbed together to prevent their
OL,12,Fchildren from receiving smartphones
OL,13,Funtil they become teenagers.
OL,15,FThe families in Woolacombe have signed
OL,16,Fa pact, promising they won't give the
OL,17,Fdevices to their children until at
OL,18,Fleast the end of Year 9, when they are
OL,19,F13 or 14 years old.
