OL,3,CThe parents who have pledged to keep
OL,4,Ctheir kids smartphone-free
OL,6,FThey hope challenging the cultural
OL,7,Fnorm could help protect their children
OL,8,Ffrom harmful material, cyberbullying
OL,9,Fand mental illness.
OL,11,FThe parents believe that, while one
OL,12,Findividual child might feel left out,
OL,13,Fif enough of them commit to the pledge
OL,14,Fthe children won't be isolated.
OL,16,FParents Joe and Jenn Steer were
OL,17,Fstruggling with the feeling that they
OL,18,Fdidn't have any choice. Jenn describes
OL,19,Fit as a "cliff edge that seemed to be
OL,20,Flooming", where everybody gives their
OL,21,Fchild a smart phone.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/8
