OL,3,CThe parents who have pledged to keep
OL,4,Ctheir kids smartphone-free
OL,6,FCampaigners say exposing children to
OL,7,Fthings their brains aren't yet
OL,8,Fdeveloped enough to deal with can
OL,9,Fcause anxiety and other mental health
OL,10,Fproblems. They also have concerns
OL,11,Fabout bullying, grooming, distraction
OL,12,Fand addiction.
OL,14,FParent Penny Clark said: "A smart
OL,15,Fphone is an adult product. It's not
OL,16,Fbeen designed for children.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/8
