OL,3,CThe parents who have pledged to keep
OL,4,Ctheir kids smartphone-free
OL,6,FHeadteacher Gail Holmes said: "We
OL,7,Fsupport children having technology and
OL,8,Fwe use technology in school. Every
OL,9,Fchild in Key Stage 2 has access to a
OL,10,FChromebook. That is their future and
OL,11,Fit's really important that they do
OL,12,Fhave those skills.
OL,14,F"This is about protecting our children
OL,15,Foutside of school, with the use of
OL,16,Fsmartphones which they don't
OL,17,Fnecessarily need. We want our children
OL,18,Fto stay children for as long as
OL,19,Fpossible and have those normal
OL,20,Fcommunications with their friends and
OL,21,Fbuild strong relationships that way."
